<HEADLINE>
FT  20 MAY 94 / International Capital Markets: Pakistan to launch eurobond
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By FARHAN BOKHARI
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   ISLAMABAD
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Pakistan is preparing to launch its first eurobond - possibly raising
Dollars 200m - in the next two months, writes Farhan Bokhari from Islamabad.
It will be the country's first attempt to convert some of its short-term
loans into medium-term borrowings. It is also keen to improve the stability
of its foreign exchange reserves.
'It is time to go to the international capital markets with a better credit
rating than is available in Pakistan and convert some six-month borrowings
into a bond,' said the Islamabad MoF.
</TEXT>
