FT  20 MAY 94 / International Company News: Job cuts and closures at P&amp;G
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By RICHARD TOMKINS
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Procter &amp; Gamble, the US consumer products group, yesterday said it was
closing three plants and shutting production lines at four other plants over
the next 30 months with the loss of 1,100 jobs.
The closures are part of the restructuring announced in July last year under
which Procter &amp; Gamble is closing 30 plants and shedding 13,000 jobs, some
12 per cent of its workforce world-wide.
Under the plans announced yesterday, the company will close the Manati
pharmaceuticals plant in Puerto Rico in 1996; the Hatboro health and beauty
care products plant in Pennsylvania by May 1996; and the Torshall throat
drop products plant in Sweden by the end of next year.
Production will be transferred to other sites. Procter &amp; Gamble said
employees would be offered early retirement, transfers or 'supportive'
severence packages. Skin care production lines will close in Mississauga,
Ontario; Hunt Valley, Maryland; and Naucalpan, Mexico.
