<HEADLINE>
FT  20 MAY 94 / International Company News: Cost-cutting aids Esselte
advance
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By CHRISTOPHER BROWN-HUMES
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Esselte, the Swedish office products group, lifted first quarter pre-tax
profits by 11 per cent as higher margins and cost-cutting helped to
compensate for lower sales.
Profit for the period totalled SKr121m (Dollars 15.7m), up from SKr109m in
the same 1993 period. Sales amounted to SKr3bn, down 2 per cent from 1993
after adjusting for exchange rates.
Mr Bo Lundquist, chief executive, said the full-year result was expected to
be better than the SKr301m achieved in 1993.
Esselte said its result had been hit by a SKr9m charge after a dispute with
a pension fund over a property deal.
</TEXT>
