<HEADLINE>
FT  20 MAY 94 / UK Company News: Fine Decor shows 44% advance to Pounds 3m
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Fine Decor, the printed wallcoverings maker and fabrics designer which came
to the market last June, lifted pre-tax profits by 44 per cent from Pounds
2.1m to Pounds 3.03m in the year to January 31.
Turnover rose to Pounds 37.6m (Pounds 33.2m) with exports contributing
Pounds 16m (Pounds 13.4m).
Earnings per share advanced to 17.16p (13.73p) and a proposed final dividend
of 3.7p makes a total of 4.7p.
On current trading Mr Roger Regan, chairman, said that first quarter sales
had been in line with the corresponding period last year, but sales
forecasts showed a stronger second half performance.
