FT  20 MAY 94 / UK Company News: Nestor Medical in management buy-out
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Nestor Medical Services, the hospital and nursing home business of
Nestor-BNA, has been sold to its management in a Pounds 14m deal structured
by 3i, the investment capital group.
3i and CINVen have co-invested about Pounds 7m of equity with senior debt
provided by Midland Bank.
The company operates four hospitals and two nursing homes.
