jumped 87 per cent to Pounds 562,000 (Pounds 301,000).
The company said the progress was helped by a large increase in marketing
and promotional efforts. It was confident that a similar level of activity
would be maintained in the second half.
Earnings per share advanced to 3.03p (2.31p). An interim dividend of 1.5p is
declared and the board expects to recommend a final of at least 2p.
The company joined the USM in December at 60p; the shares added 4p to 80p
yesterday.
