<HEADLINE>
FT  20 MAY 94 / UK Company News: Candover's Pounds 213m for new fund
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By RICHARD GOURLAY
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Candover, the venture capital group, has received commitments of Pounds 213m
for a new fund which it will invest in larger management buy-outs and
buy-ins.
The group expects to raise further capital and close the fund later this
year.
This is the first sizeable fund since Pounds 319m was raised by the group in
1989. The capital has been raised at a time when many venture capital groups
are finding it hard to persuade investors to back them with new money.
'It was easier five years ago,' said Mr Stephen Curran, chief executive. 'We
are satisfied with the progress in what is not an easy market and we are
confident there will be additional commitments in the second closing.'
The figure for the first closing includes a commitment from Candover to
invest Pounds 64m.
At the last balance sheet date Candover had Pounds 22m of cash. It expects
the imminent realisation of investments to produce the balance needed.
</TEXT>
