<TEXT>
Sir, I agree with Christopher Dunkley that 'watching television at breakfast
is depraved' (Arts: 'Mixed up breakfast menus', May 18). However, I think he
missed something when reviewing The Big Breakfast.
The Big Breakfast is refreshingly real, energetic, spontaneous and the
presenters genuine and fallible. The BBC's Business Breakfast is
appropriately professional and technically slick. However, GMTV, in its
phoney living room setting, seems to me to fall down a hole in the middle.
I suspect that GMTV is aimed at a social group that agrees watching
television at breakfast is depraved, so guess what - they don't watch it.
James Carroll,
