<HEADLINE>
FT  20 MAY 94 / Technology (Worth Watching): Sieve keeps movie films safer
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ANDREW FISHER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
The 'vinegar syndrome' is the curse of film archivists, but Kodak has
developed the Molecular Sieve to combat the deterioration of valuable motion
films in storage through moisture, temperature, acids and vapours from the
air.
The molecular sieve consists of a small sachet of zeolite, a mineral, that
absorbs moisture and chemicals. Kodak says its inclusion with processed film
in a plastic bag will extend the life of the dye images and the cellulose
triacetate film support.
Kodak: UK, 0442 61122
</TEXT>
<XX>
