<HEADLINE>
FT  20 MAY 94 / Technology (Worth Watching): Seiko, Seiko burning bright
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ANDREW FISHER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
'The brightest watch on the world market,' is the claim made by Seiko of
Japan for a new range it is launching later this year. The company's
Lumibrite technology - which dispenses with electrical energy and
fluorescent paints with small amounts of radioactive substances - provides
an initial brightness which Seiko says is up to 10 times greater than with
conventional luminous watches.
Lumibrite watches use a new Japanese pigment based mainly on aluminium
oxides. The watch dial glows brilliantly for four to five hours after 10
minutes exposure to light equivalent to the brightness in a typical office.
Seiko UK: UK, 0628 770001
