FT  20 MAY 94 / Ashdown defends stance on currency
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DAVID OWEN
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
It is in Britain's long-term economic interest to be part of a single
European currency, Mr Paddy Ashdown, the Liberal Democrat leader, said last
night.
Mr Ashdown used a speech to the cross-party European Policy Forum in London
to outline his party's stance on a range of European issues, including
defence and economic integration, before next month's European elections.
On defence, Mr Ashdown called for British resources to be pooled with other
European Union member states.
He said a common EU defence policy would produce better value for money and
a more effective response to conflicts such as the one in Bosnia.
But he said this did not mean that British troops should be sent to battle
without the consent of the UK government.
