FT  20 MAY 94 / World Trade News: Gatt still undecided on Lome regime
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By FRANCES WILLIAMS
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   GENEVA
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Nearly three years after the entry into force of the fourth Lome Convention
between the European Union and almost 70 African, Caribbean and Pacific
countries, the General Agreement on Tariffs and Trade has still not decided
whether the pact is consistent with international fair trade rules, writes
Frances Williams in Geneva.
A Gatt working party set up last year to examine Lome IV has been unable
even to agree to disagree on the issue. The EU and ACP nations are refusing
to brook any hint of criticism in the report, fearing that this could lead
to a direct challenge to Lome under Gatt's disputes settlement system.
