<HEADLINE>
FT  19 MAY 94 / International Company News: Head of Dollars 80bn US pension
fund to step down
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By RICHARD WATERS
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   NEW YORK
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Mr Dale Hanson is to step down as head of the California Public Employees
Retirement System (Calpers), the biggest US public pension plan with around
Dollars 80bn under management, it emerged yesterday.
Mr Hanson, 51, announced his intention to resign at a board meeting in
Annaheim, California yesterday.
While Calpers declined to give further reasons for Mr Hanson's departure, it
said: 'It is of his own choice. The resignation was not forced or asked for
by the board.'
Mr Hanson will explain his reasons publicly today, Calpers added.
His departure signals an upheaval in the senior management at one of the
world's biggest investment institutions. It comes just six weeks after the
retirement of Mr DeWitt Bowman, Calpers' long-standing chief investment
officer, who had built a reputation as the US's most activist shareholder.
Mr Bowman's job has in effect been left unfilled. His successor, Ms Sheryl
Pressler, a former fund manager at the McDonnell Douglas pension fund, is
not due to start work full-time at Calpers until July.
Mr Hanson is expected to announce that he will continue as chief executive
until a replacement has been found.
</TEXT>
