<HEADLINE>
FT  19 MAY 94 / London Stock Exchange: Reckitt upset
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By STEVE THOMPSON, CHRISTOPHER PRICE and JOEL KIBAZO
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Shares in household products group Reckitt &amp; Colman nosedived after the
company's chairman gave a grim message to shareholders at the annual
meeting.
Sir Michael Colman said the year had 'started slowly' and that trading was
turning out to be as difficult as in 1993.
Reckitt, trading 3 higher at 677p immediately before the meeting, dropped
sharply as the news filtered into the market, eventually closing a net 40
down at 634p. Turnover in the shares reached 3.2m, the second highest single
day's business this year.
</TEXT>
<XX>
Companies:-
</XX>
<CO>Reckitt and Colman.
</CO>
<XX>
Countries:-
</XX>
<CN>GBZ  United Kingdom, EC.
