FT  19 MAY 94 / World Stock Markets: Brazil
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
A mild inflow of foreign money to the market due to expectations of stable
US interest rates left share prices 8.6 per cent stronger on the Sao Paulo
stock exchange. The Bovespa index ended 1,425 points higher at 17,909.
Volume came to Cr296.5bn (Dollars 183.8m).
Analysts said that lower inflation forecasts, which have dragged down
Brazilian nominal long-term interest rates over the last few days, also
helped the stock market's performance. Brazil June inflation forecasts were
revised down by a full percentage point to 45.5 per cent.
