<HEADLINE>
FT  19 MAY 94 / UK Company News: Investors back change of control at Brandon
Hire
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PETER FRANKLIN
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Brandon Hire, the USM-traded tool, catering and furniture hirer which last
month announced an acquisition that could lead to a mandatory offer being
made for the company, yesterday won the necessary approvals at an EGM for
the transaction to proceed.
Under the terms of the deal Brandon is to acquire - for 3.75m new ordinary
shares - JSL Fasteners, a company formed last year by Mr John Laycock.
At the same time Mr Laycock has agreed to acquire 2.25m Brandon shares at
55p apiece from Mr Colin Stone, Brandon's joint managing director, finance
director and co-founder, who will resign with compensation for loss of
office.
Following the passing of the resolutions Mr Stone has resigned as a director
of Brandon and Mr Laycock has been appointed as chief executive.
Mr Laycock now owns or controls 6m Brandon shares - 42.5 per cent of the
enlarged share capital - and is, under the terms of the Takeover Code,
required to make a mandatory offer for the remainder of the equity.
The offer, which is priced at 55p, will close on June 8 unless declared
unconditional as to acceptances, in which case it will remain open until
June 22.
Irrevocable undertakings not to accept the offer have been received from
directors speaking for 4.95m shares - 35.04 per cent of the enlarged equity.
Imperial Pension Nominees, Brandon's largest outside shareholder, has also
undertaken not to accept in respect of its holding of 785,000 shares - 5.5
per cent.
Brandon's shares closed up 3p at 71p.
</TEXT>
