Yesterday, the trade and industry select committee was able to consult two
witnesses in Washington DC.
Heaven forbid, if this habit catches on, that it could herald the end of all
those overseas jollies - sorry, overseas fact-finding visits - when MPs head
for the sun at the expense of the British taxpayer.
