FT  19 MAY 94 / Observer: Berlusconi's own goal
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Win or lose, the footballers of Milan, Italy's league champions, have grown
accustomed to the personal support of one Silvio Berlusconi, the club's
owner and president. But last night even Berlusconi had to concede that
there were more important places to be than Athens's Olympic stadium, where
Milan and Barcelona were playing what had been billed as a 'dream final' of
the European Cup.
Instead, Italy's new premier was on the terraces of the upper house of the
Italian parliament, egging on his government team to win a crucial vote of
confidence.
While the media magnate has publicly pledged not to give up the reins of the
club, there are already calls for him to distance himself from his favourite
toy. But it will be a brave adviser who suggests, say, that he become
honorary president. Berlusconi may have lost interest in the running of his
Fininvest empire since entering politics, but his devotion to the soccer
club is said still to border on the religious.
