<HEADLINE>
FT  19 MAY 94 / People: Top Management Programme
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The government's Top Management Programme, which brings together high fliers
from the public and private sector, has a new programme director in Hugh
Taylor, a Grade 3 at the Cabinet Office.
Taylor, 44, is currently serving as head of the Cabinet Office Management
Development Group. Previously he was at the Home Office, with responsibility
for personnel management in the Prison Service.
Taylor replaces Marianne Neville-Rolfe who has become director of the
government's new north-west regional office. Neville-Rolfe's other job as
head of the Civil Service College has also been filled recently by Stephen
Hickey, formerly head of a planning and finance branch in the Department of
Social Security.
Hickey, 44, joined the DSS after leaving Oxford and has worked in the
department ever since, apart from a secondment to Rank Xerox (UK). In 1988,
he headed the team that recommended the creation of agencies to take over
most of the department's executive functions.
