<HEADLINE>
FT  19 MAY 94 / Channel 4 loses programme battle
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Channel 4 has failed in the first round of its battle to take the
Broadcasting Complaints Commission to judicial review over a programme
involving two former chancellors of the exchequer, Lords Lawson and Howe.
Mr Justice Popplewell has refused Channel 4 permission to go to judicial
review after looking at written submissions.
However Mr Michael Grade, Channel 4 chief executive, is determined now to
seek a full hearing.
The row between the channel and the BCC is over a programme on monetary
policy, A Brief Economic History of Our Times, made by Fulcrum Productions.
The commission found that the programme was accurate but decided that if the
two Conservative peers had known how critical the programme was going to be
of their handling of the economy, they would not have agreed to take part.
