<HEADLINE>
FT  19 MAY 94 / Shell to expand research centre
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Shell is to spend Pounds 70m over seven years modernising and expanding its
main UK research centre at Thornton, Cheshire.
Thornton, which is one of the largest of Shell's 15 complexes of industrial
laboratories worldwide, currently employs 600 staff. By the end of next year
it will take in 140 scientists from a centre in Sittingbourne, Kent, which
Shell is closing.
The Cheshire centre's best known work is on automotive fuels and lubricating
oils.
It has also become one of the world's foremost centres for combustion
science and hazard analysis, where its work on gas explosions in confined
spaces has enabled safer design of offshore oil and gas platforms since the
Piper Alpha disaster in 1988.
