<HEADLINE>
FT  19 MAY 94 / Car sales only slightly dented
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
April's tax increases had only a slightly damping effect on the upsurge in
both new and used car sales, according to statistics from HPI, the vehicle
finance information agency.
Sales of new cars bought on hire purchase or other forms of instalment
finance were 11.2 per cent higher in April than in the corresponding month
last year, and finance sales of used cars 10 per cent higher, according to
HPI. However, both represented a slowdown compared with first-quarter growth
of 28.8 per cent year-on-year for sales of new cars bought on instalments
and 15.1 per cent for used-car sales.
The instalment purchase figures compare with a 4.8 per cent year-on-year
increase in total new-car sales in April. 'It seems that the market for cars
bought on finance terms has withstood the effect of April's tax increases
better than cash purchases,' said Dr Brian Bailey, HPI chairman.
</TEXT>
